    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Filling the fibers of light leather, such as that used for gloves, with an emulsion of oils or grease and water to make the fibers water-repellent and flexible; distinguished from "currying," which is introducing fatty substances into heavy leather.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Llenado de las fibras de un cuero ligero, tal como el utilizado para guantes, con una emulsión de aceites o grasa y agua para que las fibras sean repelentes al agua y flexibles. Se diferencia de "sobado", que es la introducción de sustancias grasas en cuero pesado.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Het vullen van de vezels van licht leer, zoals het leer dat wordt gebruikt voor handschoenen, met een emulsie van oliën of vet en water om de vezels waterafstotend en flexibel te maken; wordt onderscheiden van 'touwen', het introduceren van vettige substanties in zwaar leer.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099099/Van Dale groot woordenboek (1994)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>將油脂或動物油脂及水製成之乳化劑，注滿手套用皮革等輕革纖維，讓皮革纖維具有彈性且防水；不同於專指讓厚革吸收油脂物質的「加脂操作」。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
